And I'm seeing things,
uncomfortable things,

75
00:06:52,146 --> 00:06:55,680
and they're in my dreams.
They're fast and furious.

76
00:06:55,682 --> 00:06:59,584
And I'm just-- I'm feeling really really weird here.

77
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:04,423
What?
You don't think I should take them?

78
00:07:04,425 --> 00:07:08,693
No, it's not that,
but do you remember the side effects?

79
00:07:08,695 --> 00:07:10,729
You never wanted
to take them.

80
00:07:10,731 --> 00:07:13,131
I mean,
your nightmares got so bad.

81
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:15,967
I don't think you even remember,
but one time, you were choking.

82
00:07:15,969 --> 00:07:18,804
I know, I know, okay.
You don't have to remind me, okay?

83
00:07:18,806 --> 00:07:20,605
You don't have to keep
bringing it up.

84
00:07:20,607 --> 00:07:23,642
It's just one small
piece of the past.

85
00:07:23,644 --> 00:07:26,311
It's just,
I never should have-- Gotten together?

86
00:07:26,313 --> 00:07:27,712
Moved in together?

87
00:07:27,714 --> 00:07:33,185
No. Not at all.
You're the best.

88
00:07:33,187 --> 00:07:36,221
You're the one thing that's keeping
me from going completely insane.

89
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:45,197
Lizzy, it's just a house
and it's yours.

90
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:47,132
I am so confused.

91
00:07:47,134 --> 00:07:50,335
When Dr. Fredricks
recommended this...

92
00:07:50,337 --> 00:07:52,337
they took care
of everything.

93
00:07:52,339 --> 00:07:54,139
They, who is they?

94
00:07:56,676 --> 00:07:58,777
The lawyers? The lawyers
took care of everything?

95
00:08:02,248 --> 00:08:04,850
Honey, you don't even remember living here.

96
00:08:04,852 --> 00:08:07,185
No, I know,
but I should.

97
00:08:07,187 --> 00:08:10,155
From what they told me,
I was living here when I was just a child.

98
00:08:10,157 --> 00:08:12,724
Just let it go.

99
00:08:12,726 --> 00:08:15,494
Like you said,
it's part of the past.

100
00:08:15,496 --> 00:08:17,229
It's just you
and me now.

101
00:08:17,231 --> 00:08:19,297
[Kisses her]

102
00:08:19,299 --> 00:08:23,034
Dr, Fredricks said something
happened to me in this house.

103
00:08:26,138 --> 00:08:27,672
And now I'm back.

104
00:08:30,142 --> 00:08:32,277
I just-- I want out of that house!

105
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:35,247
Hmm, well, Lizzy,
it sounds like your childhood environment

106
00:08:35,249 --> 00:08:39,117
is triggering some memories,
as unpleasant as they may be.

107
00:08:39,119 --> 00:08:41,486
No! There's something going on in the house.
I know it!

108
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:43,655
Well, okay,
that's something.

109
00:08:43,657 --> 00:08:45,223
I know what
you're going to say.

110
00:08:45,225 --> 00:08:46,825
I don't want to sound
like a broken record,

111
00:08:46,827 --> 00:08:48,159
but we've been
down this road.

112
00:08:48,161 --> 00:08:50,028
It wasn't
a daydream.

113
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:52,831
Okay? I mean,
it was, but it wasn't.

114
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:55,534
What do you mean
It wasn't?

115
00:08:55,536 --> 00:08:57,235
It just--
it seemed so real.

116
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:01,206
You know,
it's very hard to explain,

117
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:04,242
but it wasn't-- it wasn't fuzzy or dreamlike,

118
00:09:04,244 --> 00:09:07,579
It's like I was really there, and--

119
00:09:07,581 --> 00:09:09,481
[sighs]
I don't know.

120
00:09:09,483 --> 00:09:11,516
I was really surprised when I woke up in the morning.

121
00:09:11,518 --> 00:09:13,118
I didn't even have
that much to drink.

122
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:16,254
Have you-- have you
been taking your pills?

123
00:09:16,256 --> 00:09:21,226
Yes. Well, I stopped taking them
for a while because of Jason,

124
00:09:21,228 --> 00:09:23,728
but I just started taking them again

125
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:28,700
And I thought that
the daydreams would stop

126
00:09:28,702 --> 00:09:30,535
when I started
taking them again,

127
00:09:30,537 --> 00:09:31,836
but I guess I'm
still having them?

128
00:09:31,838 --> 00:09:33,605
I don't know.

129
00:09:33,607 --> 00:09:36,374
How does Jason
feel about all of this?

130
00:09:36,376 --> 00:09:38,109
Jason thinks I'm crazy.

131
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:43,915
No, he's been very,
very supportive,

132
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:46,251
and I can tell that he is
very worried about me.

133
00:09:46,253 --> 00:09:54,426
Lizzy, what would you say
if you were in my shoes?

134
00:09:54,428 --> 00:09:55,860
"This visit's on me"?

135
00:09:58,798 --> 00:10:00,799
No, I'm serious.

136
00:10:00,801 --> 00:10:02,634
[Lizzy laughing]

137
00:10:04,704 --> 00:10:10,575
Seriously. I would
probably say that

138
00:10:10,577 --> 00:10:15,313
you're just stressed out and tired

139
00:10:15,315 --> 00:10:17,816
and having really bad nightmares or daydreams.

140
00:10:17,818 --> 00:10:19,417
How about you
just lost your job,

141
00:10:19,419 --> 00:10:20,952
you've got a new boyfriend,

142
00:10:20,954 --> 00:10:22,587
you just moved back
into your old house,

143
00:10:22,589 --> 00:10:25,523
all, what, in the course
of a year.

144
00:10:25,525 --> 00:10:30,395
Those are some serious life changes in a very,
very short amount of time.

145
00:10:30,397 --> 00:10:35,100
And the stress that has followed
brings up all these childhood memories

146
00:10:35,102 --> 00:10:36,768
which weren't perfect
to begin with.

147
00:10:38,537 --> 00:10:40,338
Huh?
Yeah.

148
00:10:43,743 --> 00:10:46,144
Why do you think
that you can't remember?

149
00:10:49,081 --> 00:10:51,316
Where are those memories?

150
00:11:24,483 --> 00:11:28,219
I am going to dip
my wick in your candy pool?

151
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:48,800
What an ugly doll.

152
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:25,770
[Pretend English accent] I might say,
your dress is quite lovely.

153
00:13:25,772 --> 00:13:28,206
Where on earth
did you find it?

154
00:13:29,608 --> 00:13:32,844
[Eerie, scattered voice]

155
00:13:32,846 --> 00:13:37,048
Really, I do!
They are so marvelous.

156
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:39,784
My mother shopped
there for years.

157
00:13:39,786 --> 00:13:42,187
[Scattered, eerie voice]

158
00:13:42,189 --> 00:13:49,060
He what? I don't know
if Thomas likes me, or not.

159
00:13:50,496 --> 00:13:53,865
Did he ask you
about me or something?

160
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:56,501
[Scattered voice]

161
00:13:58,103 --> 00:14:00,371
He said what?

162
00:14:00,373 --> 00:14:02,740
[Scattered voice]

163
00:14:02,742 --> 00:14:04,275
He did?

164
00:14:04,277 --> 00:14:09,113
I'm so happy!
How is your tea, Suzy?

165
00:14:09,115 --> 00:14:11,749
Do you want some more?
[Scattered voice]

166
00:14:11,751 --> 00:14:13,952
Great!

167
00:14:28,133 --> 00:14:35,240
[Man] Lizzy!
[Scattered voices]

168
00:14:35,242 --> 00:14:38,042
[pants]

169
